Package camzup.core

Class Bounds3

java.lang.Object
camzup.core.Bounds3
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Bounds3>
public class Bounds3 extends Object implements Comparable<Bounds3>
An axis aligned bounding box (AABB) for a 3D volume, represented with a minimum and maximum coordinate.

    • split

      public static void split(Bounds3 b, float xFac, float yFac, float zFac, Bounds3 bsw, Bounds3 bse, Bounds3 bnw, Bounds3 bne, Bounds3 fsw, Bounds3 fse, Bounds3 fnw, Bounds3 fne)
      Splits a bounding volume into eight octants according to three factors in the range [0.0, 1.0] . The factor on the x axis governs the vertical split; on the y axis, the horizontal split; on the z axis, the depth split.
      Parameters:
      b - the bounds
      xFac - vertical factor
      yFac - horizontal factor
      zFac - depth factor
      bsw - back south west
      bse - back south east
      bnw - back north west
      bne - back north east
      fsw - front south west
      fse - front south east
      fnw - front north west
      fne - front north east

      • Utils.clamp(float, float, float)

    • split

      public static boolean split(Bounds3 b, Vec3 v, Bounds3 bsw, Bounds3 bse, Bounds3 bnw, Bounds3 bne, Bounds3 fsw, Bounds3 fse, Bounds3 fnw, Bounds3 fne)
      Splits a bounding volume into eight octants according to a point. If the point is inside the bounding volume, assigns the result to target bounds and returns true. If the point is outside the bounding volume, returns false.

      fne - front north east
      Returns:
      point is in bounds
